  "body": "### Description\r\nThe standalone VC defaults to `--network=auto` and if that's changed to a specific network prints a deprecation warning:\r\n```\r\nDEPRECATION WARNING: The '--network=prater' option is deprecated. Use '--network=auto' instead, which fetches network configuration from the beacon node endpoint.\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt turns out though that while using `auto` is nice and simple, it has a couple of downsides:\r\n\r\n1. There can be incompatibilities with the beacon node's config endpoint - e.g. Lighthouse forgot to add a new constant from Bellatrix which meant Teku refused to parse the config. It worked when an explicit network was specified\r\n2. If the VC is upgraded before the beacon node, it can be running a version we say is ready for an upcoming hard fork, but have loaded the old config from the beacon node and won't actually be ready until the beacon node is updated *and* the VC is restarted again\r\n\r\nAs a result, for a lot of situations it is actually better to explicitly specify the network. Suggestion is to leave the default as `auto` but remove the deprecation warning, leaving it as a permanently supported option (also remove any reference to it being deprecated from the changelog).",
